    "narrative": "Today\u2019s lineup for the Austin Waves is anchored by **Gunnar Henderson**, whose 81.88 efficiency score makes him our clear offensive engine. Facing McCullers Jr. (4.94 xERA), **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a massive park-factor boost (+16%) and a favorable matchup against a pitcher with a slow delivery that essentially gift-wraps an opportunity for a stolen base. Close behind is **Jacob Wilson**, riding a 71.63 score into a prime leadoff spot against Cameron. His aggressive position in the order combined with a 10% park boost makes him a high-floor play, particularly as we hunt for counting stats in a matchup where we expect him to be on base early and often. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (67.95) also offers a strong profile; despite a slight platoon disadvantage against Ober, his high xwOBA and middle-of-the-order protection keep him firmly in \"Strong\" start territory.\n\nThe decision-making process for the remaining slots focused heavily on speed and efficiency. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (59.83) narrowly missed the \"Strong\" tier but remains a start due to a significant 14% platoon edge against Peralta. Meanwhile, **Nasim Nunez** (45.93) serves as our tactical SB specialist; while his raw offensive output is marginal, his sub-40 exclusion risk is mitigated by the 92% SB efficiency probability against Peralta\u2019s delivery, keeping him in the lineup to protect our standing in the league's scarcest category. **Drake Baldwin** (53.50) and **Heliot Ramos** (53.76) round out the rotation as serviceable plays, though they lack the high-ceiling upside of the top half of our order. With **Kyle Tucker**, **Jackson Merrill**, and **Andy Pages** all on off-days, and **Luis Robert Jr.** sidelined on the IL, the bench remained static, meaning we are relying on our depth players like **Jordan Westburg**, **Jorge Polanco**, and **Josh Lowe** to stay ready for tomorrow\u2019s rotation. No significant weather hazards are flagged for today\u2019s slate, allowing us to proceed with our projected lineup without fear of mid-game disruptions.",
